As part of efforts to raise capital for the 2020 budget, the Federal Government will offer a five, 10 and 30 year bonds at 12.7 percent, 14.5 percent 14.8 percent interest rates respectively. This was contained in a document published on the Debt Management Office (DMO) website on Wednesday. The document showed the breakdown of the N155 billion bond to include a N50bn five-year reopening bond that would mature in April 2023, a N50bn 10-year reopening bond that would mature in April 2029 and N55bn 30-year bond expected to mature in April 2049. The document also showed that the auction date is January 22, 2020 and the settlement date is January 24, 2020. FG to auction bonds at 14% FG to auction N145bn long term bonds at 14% FG to auction long term bonds at 14 %